instruction:
In triangle $ABC$, shown below, $AC = \sqrt{20}$ and $AB = 4$. What is $\tan A$?

[asy]
pair A,B,C;
B = (0,0);
A = (0,4);
C = (2,0);
draw(A--B--C--A);
draw(rightanglemark(A,B,C,7));
label("$B$",B,SW);
label("$A$",A,NW);
label("$C$",C,SE);
label("$4$",(A+B)/2,NW);
label("$\sqrt{20}$",(A+C)/2,NE);
[/asy]

Let \( S \) be a set with 2002 elements, and \( N \) be an integer such that \( 0 \leqslant N \leqslant 2^{2002} \). Prove that it is possible to color all subsets of \( S \) either black or white such that the following conditions hold:
1. The union of any two white subsets is white;
2. The union of any two black subsets is black;
3. There are exactly \( N \) white subsets.

(This problem is from the 31st USAMO.)

Let the function $f(x)=\tan \frac {x}{4}\cdot \cos ^{2} \frac {x}{4}-2\cos ^{2}\left( \frac {x}{4}+ \frac {\pi}{12}\right)+1$.

(Ⅰ) Find the domain of $f(x)$ and its smallest positive period;

(Ⅱ) Find the maximum and minimum values of $f(x)$ in the interval $[-\pi,0]$.

Given the daily sales volume of a product, $y$ (in tons), in relation to its sale price, $x$ (in ten thousand yuan per ton, $1 < x \leq 5$), follows the relationship: When $1 < x \leq 3$, $y = a(x - 4)^2 + \frac{6}{x-1}$ (where $a$ is a constant); when $3 < x \leq 5$, $y = kx + 7$ (where $k < 0$). It is known that when the sale price is 3 ten thousand yuan per ton, 4 tons of the product can be sold daily, and when the sale price $x \in (3, 5]$ the lowest sales volume is 2 tons.
(1) Determine the values of $a$ and $k$, and establish the analytic expression of $y$ as a function of $x$;
(2) If the cost of the product is 1 ten thousand yuan per ton, find the value of the selling price $x$ that maximizes the daily profit from selling the product.

Given the function $f(x)=x^{2}+3x-3-ke^{x}$.  
$(I)$ When $x \geqslant -5$, $f(x) \leqslant 0$, find the range of values for $k$;  
$(II)$ When $k=-1$, prove that: $f(x) > -6$.

A plot of land is sown with seeds of smooth brome. On one section of this plot, weeds make up $0.4\%$ of the vegetation. What is the probability that among 125 plants randomly selected from this section, there are:

a) exactly 3 weeds;

b) no more than 3 weeds.

Solve the inequality:
(1) $\frac{x-4}{x+3} \geq 0$;
(2) $\frac{x^{2}-6 x+8}{x^{2}+5 x+6} \leq 0$.

Simplify:  
$(1)(a^{2})^{3}+3a^{4}\cdot a^{2}-a^{8}\div a^{2}$;  
$(2)\left(x-3\right)\left(x+4\right)-x\left(x+3\right)$.

A solid right prism $PQRSUV$ has a height of 18, as shown. Also, its bases are equilateral triangles with side length 10. Points $M$, $N$, and $O$ are the midpoints of edges $PQ$, $QR$, and $PR$, respectively. Determine the perimeter of triangle $MNO$. [asy]
pair P, Q, R, S, U, V, M, N, O;
P=(0,0);
Q=(10,0);
R=(5,-5);
S=(5,-23);
U=(0,-18);
V=(10,-18);
M=(P+Q)/2;
N=(Q+R)/2;
O=(R+P)/2;
draw(P--Q--R--P--U--S--V--Q--R--S);
draw(M--N--O--M, dashed);
label("$P$", P, NW);
label("$Q$", Q, NE);
label("$R$", R, N);
label("$S$", S, S);
label("$U$", U, SW);
label("$V$", V, SE);
label("$M$", M, SW);
label("$N$", N, SE);
label("$O$", O, SE);
label("10", (P+Q)/2, dir(90));
label("18", (P+V)/2, dir(0));
[/asy]

