Among the following propositions: 
- (1) "If $ac^{2} < bc^{2}$, then $a < b$" is the negation of the proposition;
- (2) The contrapositive of "If $m > 0$, then the equation $x^{2} + x - m = 0$ has real roots";
- (3) The negation of "There exists a quadrilateral that does not have a circumscribed circle";
- (4) "$ab \neq 0$ is a sufficient condition for $a \neq 0$.
